Updation in Round 2
This file explains the changes made in Round 2 of the FairRide project.  
In this round, the main aim was to add better features, improve the design, and make the project feel more like a real application.

--------------------------------------------------

1. New Features

- Added Google Maps search with location suggestions and current location option  
- Added user login using Email or Phone OTP  
- Previous trips are now saved automatically  
- Users can see price comparison and estimated savings  
- Favourite routes, price alerts, sharing, and PDF download options are added  

--------------------------------------------------

2. UI and UX Improvements

- Design is improved using cards and gradient backgrounds  
- Simple animations are added for better interaction  
- Loading screens, price charts, and real logos are used  
- Dark mode and light mode options are available  
- Mobile-friendly layout with bottom navigation and swipe support  

--------------------------------------------------

3. Live Tracking and Pricing

- Live cab movement is shown on the map  
- Multiple cabs are displayed for each provider  
- Availability is shown using a heatmap  
- Traffic is shown on the map  
- Prices update automatically and surge pricing is simulated  

--------------------------------------------------

4. Feature Priority (Round 2)

High Priority (Week 1)  
- Live tracking and map-related features  

Medium Priority (Week 1)  
- UI improvements and dark mode  

Low Priority (Week 2)  
- User login, trip history, and favourite routes  

--------------------------------------------------

5. Tech Stack Used

- Frontend: React / Next.js  
- Maps: Google Maps API  
- Styling: Tailwind CSS  
- Backend (Mock): Node.js / Firebase  
- Database: Firebase / MongoDB  

--------------------------------------------------

6. Goal of Round 2

The goal of this round was to make FairRide easier to use, more interactive, and closer to a real-world cab comparison system.

--------------------------------------------------

7. Next Steps

- Add real cab provider APIs  
- Improve price prediction  
- Support more cities  

--------------------------------------------------

Thank you for checking the Round 2 updates of FairRide.
